<p>Well, actually itâ€™s already been a while since I launched this new design (October 2021 <img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/1f605.png" alt="ðŸ˜…" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" />), but without any comment.</p>



<p>But I think itâ€™s not too late to still write a little post about it.</p>



<h2>The goal: make the blog look like the rest of lgk.io</h2>



<p>The blog runs with WordPress and now with a new child theme of the preinstalled Twenty Twenty-One, I just called â€žTwenty Twenty-One LGKâ€œ. In the past I used a theme I totally created myself, it was called â€žWinegumâ€œ. Itâ€™s still available on GitHub (<a href="https://github.com/lgkonline/Winegum1" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">https://github.com/lgkonline/Winegum1</a>), but I really donâ€™t recommend to use it anymore. Itâ€™s very outdated not compatible with modern WordPress features and third-party plugins. It might also be better for security reasons to use a theme, which is activity maintained. Thatâ€™s why I switched to Twenty Twenty-One.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://blog-static.lgk.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bildschirmfoto-2022-03-08-um-15.38.48.png"><img width="1024" height="680" src="https://blog-static.lgk.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bildschirmfoto-2022-03-08-um-15.38.48-1024x680.png" alt="" class="wp-image-2314" srcset="https://blog-static.lgk.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bildschirmfoto-2022-03-08-um-15.38.48-1024x680.png 1024w, https://blog-static.lgk.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bildschirmfoto-2022-03-08-um-15.38.48-300x199.png 300w, https://blog-static.lgk.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bildschirmfoto-2022-03-08-um-15.38.48-768x510.png 768w, https://blog-static.lgk.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bildschirmfoto-2022-03-08-um-15.38.48-1536x1020.png 1536w, https://blog-static.lgk.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bildschirmfoto-2022-03-08-um-15.38.48-2048x1360.png 2048w, https://blog-static.lgk.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bildschirmfoto-2022-03-08-um-15.38.48-1568x1042.png 1568w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></a><figcaption>Previous look with Twenty Twenty-One</figcaption></figure>



<p>I used the color customisation options of the theme to make it match better with my&nbsp;<a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://lgk.io/" target="_blank">portfolio site</a>. That was the first step to the current look of the blog. From there I created my child theme and replaced parts of the theme, most important part is the header.</p>



<p>By the way: my portfolio site and this blog are running on completely different technologies. The blog is a PHP-server-rendered WordPress site and my portfolio is a React Single-Page-Application. So my task was to bring the header of my React app to the WordPress theme and make it look as seamless as possible.</p>



<p>Iâ€™m pretty happy with the result. When you switch between â€žBlogâ€œ and â€žStartâ€œ for example, you are switching between two totally separated sites, hopefully without mentioning it. The blog uses the same colors and the same font now.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://blog-static.lgk.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bildschirmfoto-2022-03-09-um-07.56.48.png"><img loading="lazy" width="1024" height="608" src="https://blog-static.lgk.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bildschirmfoto-2022-03-09-um-07.56.48-1024x608.png" alt="" class="wp-image-2316" srcset="https://blog-static.lgk.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bildschirmfoto-2022-03-09-um-07.56.48-1024x608.png 1024w, https://blog-static.lgk.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bildschirmfoto-2022-03-09-um-07.56.48-300x178.png 300w, https://blog-static.lgk.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bildschirmfoto-2022-03-09-um-07.56.48-768x456.png 768w, https://blog-static.lgk.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bildschirmfoto-2022-03-09-um-07.56.48-1536x912.png 1536w, https://blog-static.lgk.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bildschirmfoto-2022-03-09-um-07.56.48-2048x1215.png 2048w, https://blog-static.lgk.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bildschirmfoto-2022-03-09-um-07.56.48-1568x931.png 1568w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></a><figcaption>This is how the blog looked like until I switched to Twenty Twenty-One</figcaption></figure>



<h2>The new search bar</h2>



<p>One thing was still missing on the new theme: a search bar. <img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/1f648.png" alt="ðŸ™ˆ" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> But hey, better late than never, right? Itâ€™s now there too!</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://blog-static.lgk.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bildschirmfoto-2022-03-08-um-16.02.12.png"><img loading="lazy" width="1024" height="502" src="https://blog-static.lgk.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bildschirmfoto-2022-03-08-um-16.02.12-1024x502.png" alt="" class="wp-image-2315" srcset="https://blog-static.lgk.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bildschirmfoto-2022-03-08-um-16.02.12-1024x502.png 1024w, https://blog-static.lgk.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bildschirmfoto-2022-03-08-um-16.02.12-300x147.png 300w, https://blog-static.lgk.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bildschirmfoto-2022-03-08-um-16.02.12-768x377.png 768w, https://blog-static.lgk.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bildschirmfoto-2022-03-08-um-16.02.12-1536x753.png 1536w, https://blog-static.lgk.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bildschirmfoto-2022-03-08-um-16.02.12-1568x769.png 1568w, https://blog-static.lgk.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bildschirmfoto-2022-03-08-um-16.02.12.png 1966w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></a><figcaption>The new search component on the start page</figcaption></figure>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://blog-static.lgk.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bildschirmfoto-2022-03-08-um-16.02.26.png"><img loading="lazy" width="1024" height="502" src="https://blog-static.lgk.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bildschirmfoto-2022-03-08-um-16.02.26-1024x502.png" alt="" class="wp-image-2328" srcset="https://blog-static.lgk.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bildschirmfoto-2022-03-08-um-16.02.26-1024x502.png 1024w, https://blog-static.lgk.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bildschirmfoto-2022-03-08-um-16.02.26-300x147.png 300w, https://blog-static.lgk.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bildschirmfoto-2022-03-08-um-16.02.26-768x377.png 768w, https://blog-static.lgk.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bildschirmfoto-2022-03-08-um-16.02.26-1536x753.png 1536w, https://blog-static.lgk.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bildschirmfoto-2022-03-08-um-16.02.26-1568x769.png 1568w, https://blog-static.lgk.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bildschirmfoto-2022-03-08-um-16.02.26.png 1966w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></a><figcaption>Search bar appears when you click on the magnifying glass icon</figcaption></figure>



<p>This was actually a more difficult because I had to use some JavaScript here. I started coding the search bar on my portfolio and then brought it to the blog theme as a small React app only for the search bar. The search bar is just executing a simple WordPress search request (https://blog-static.lgk.io/?s=<strong>my+request</strong>). Right now, the request only shows results from my blog. It would be awesome, to also show results from my portfolio site. Maybe I will bring that in the future when I have time. ^^</p>
